═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
GROUND RULES — enforce throughout every component
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

TYPESCRIPT
- Zero `any`. Every prop, state, ref, and event handler is fully typed.
- All component props have explicit interfaces defined above the component.
- Use React.FC<Props> or function syntax with explicit return type.

SERVER VS CLIENT COMPONENTS
- Default to React Server Components (RSC). No 'use client' unless the
  component uses: useState, useEffect, useRef, event handlers,
  browser APIs, or Framer Motion animations.
- Animated wrappers get 'use client'. Their data-fetching parents stay server.
- Pattern: ServerSection fetches/passes data → ClientAnimatedShell renders it.

TAILWIND
- Use CSS custom properties (var(--primary), var(--muted), etc.) from
  globals.css for all colors. Never hardcode hex values in className.
- All spacing via Tailwind scale. No arbitrary values except for precise
  measurements that cannot be expressed otherwise (e.g. h-[1px]).
- Mobile-first: every component works at 375px before adding md: lg: xl:

ANIMATIONS (Framer Motion)
- All entrance animations use a shared variants object — not inline.
- Standard entrance: fadeInUp — opacity 0→1, y 24→0, duration 0.5,
  ease: [0.21, 0.47, 0.32, 0.98] (custom cubic bezier, feels physical).
- Stagger children: staggerChildren: 0.08 on the container.
- Scroll-triggered: use whileInView, viewport: { once: true, amount: 0.2 }
  so animations fire once and don't repeat on scroll-back.
- NO animations on layout-critical elements (nav, headings above the fold).
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion: wrap all motion components with a check.

ACCESSIBILITY
- Every section has a semantic <section> tag with aria-labelledby pointing
  to its heading id.
- All interactive elements are keyboard navigable with visible focus rings
  (use ring-2 ring-primary ring-offset-2).
- Images: next/image with descriptive alt text always.
- Icon-only buttons: aria-label always.
- Color contrast: text must meet WCAG AA (4.5:1) in both light and dark mode.

SECTION ANATOMY
Every section follows this pattern:
  <section id="{name}" aria-labelledby="{name}-heading" className="py-24 lg:py-32">
    <div className="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-6xl">
      <SectionHeader id="{name}-heading" label="..." title="..." subtitle="..." />
      {/* content */}
    </div>
  </section>

