           leading-[1.1], text-foreground
  - subtitle: text-base md:text-lg, text-muted-foreground, max-w-2xl,
              leading-relaxed, mt-4
  - Spacing: label → title gap: mt-3. Title → subtitle gap: mt-4.
  - Bottom margin of the whole header before section content: mb-12 lg:mb-16
  - Animate label and title separately with staggered fadeInUp.

── components/ui/TechBadge.tsx ────────────────────────────

Props: name: string, variant?: 'default' | 'outline' | 'ghost'

A small pill showing a technology name. Examples: "Next.js", "TypeScript".
- default: bg-primary/10 text-primary border border-primary/20
- outline: border border-border text-muted-foreground bg-transparent
- ghost: bg-muted text-muted-foreground no border
- Size: text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full font-medium
- Subtle hover: hover:bg-primary/20 transition-colors duration-150
- No icon needed (keeps it clean and fast to render in lists)

── components/ui/AnimatedSection.tsx ──────────────────────

'use client'
A wrapper that provides scroll-triggered fadeInUp for any section content.
Props: children, className?, delay?: number

Uses Framer Motion motion.div with:
  initial: { opacity: 0, y: 24 }
  whileInView: { opacity: 1, y: 0 }
  viewport: { once: true, amount: 0.15 }
  transition: { duration: 0.5, ease: [0.21, 0.47, 0.32, 0.98], delay }

Check useReducedMotion() — if true, render children directly without motion.

── components/ui/GradientText.tsx ─────────────────────────

'use client'
Wraps text in a CSS gradient using the primary color.
  className="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary to-primary/60 bg-clip-text
             text-transparent"
Used sparingly — only for the name in Hero and 1–2 section titles max.

── lib/animations.ts ──────────────────────────────────────

Export all shared Framer Motion variants so every component imports from
one place. Never define variants inline in components.

Export:
  fadeInUp         — standard entrance (opacity+y as above)
  fadeIn           — opacity only, no y movement
  staggerContainer — staggerChildren: 0.08, delayChildren: 0.1
  slideInLeft      — for timeline items: x: -20 → 0
  scaleIn          — for cards on hover: scale 0.97 → 1
  containerVariants — combines staggerContainer with fadeIn for lists

